class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="neo-reach" class="entry-website-title">NeoReach</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website NeoReach"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://neoreach.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://neoreach.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>San Francisco, California, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>NeoReach is a San Francisco-based marketing agency that specializes in end-to-end influencer marketing solutions, as well as paid media and market research services. The website provides a fun and professional online presence with clean design elements accentuated by whimsical animations and soft color accents.</p><p>Potential clients can peruse the site's well-organized content, which includes managed services, pricing plans, and case studies, to get a better sense of the agency's capabilities. There is also an online messaging tool for users to easily connect with an expert.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website has a modern appearance with ample white space that allows the content-rich page sections to shine. The site also features a wide variety of resources, such as blog posts and infographics, to give visitors a comprehensive overview of the marketing industry.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE picked up several incidents of insufficient contrast ratios throughout the site, which can be rectified with a darker color palette. The website is missing a dedicated customer reviews section, and the repetition of some images may distract from the site's visual appeal.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop website is both functional and visually appealing with easy site navigation and refined aesthetics. Users can easily send an inquiry to the company with clear CTA buttons and an intuitive online form, while the prominent social media links ensure optimal engagement.</p><p>However, in terms of readability, the website's body text is quite small and should be sized up for a more seamless user experience. On Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the desktop version has a 99/100 performance score.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-neoreach-20240613-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile website also has a high-performance score of 92/100, likely due to fast page loading times and user-friendly navigation. The site retains its clean and contemporary look on mobile, using ample white space to create a good balance between content and images. However, a downfall is the hidden CTA button that should be added to the home page for additional prominence.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="well-done-marketing" class="entry-website-title">Well Done Marketing</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-3840x9179-20240613.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-3840x9179-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-3840x9179-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Well Done Marketing"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.welldonemarketing.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.welldonemarketing.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Indianapolis, Indiana, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Well Done Marketing is a full-service agency that provides local clients with end-to-end marketing consulting, branding, and communications solutions. The website conveys the company's multifaceted approach to projects with dynamic visual elements, such as an introductory home page video, and engaging content, which includes a portfolio of completed projects.</p><p>The use of a strong hero image gives visitors a good overview of the agency's commitment to creating fun and cohesive user experiences.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The home page features an eye-catching video that captures the essence of the company's branding philosophy. The "Meet The Team" section showcases the agency's varied team and assures clients of their diverse design and marketing perspectives. According to WAVE, the site has few contrast errors.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The website does not feature a dedicated client reviews and/or testimonials section. The company name is also not immediately visible on the home page, which could be confusing to first-time visitors.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-3840x9179-20240613.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-3840x9179-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site effectively captures the agency's blend of traditional and digital marketing with unique design elements that feel both retro-inspired and modern. Site navigation is straightforward, albeit the site swaps a full top menu bar for a hamburger menu. In terms of clear calls to action, the website would benefit from additional, perhaps larger buttons to entice users to connect with the agency.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-824x9303-20240613.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-well-done-marketing-824x9303-20240613.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile website scales all content and images appropriately, ensuring visitors can easily access the company's introductory video and other important information. Site navigation also remains user-friendly but as with its desktop counterpart, the mobile version could benefit from additional CTA buttons. On Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the site's performance score is rather low at 48/100, but its SEO practices are optimal at 92/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
